div.p:
2. Consider that as it cost Christ many milions of prayers and groans, and sighs, so he is now at this instant and hath been for these 1600 years night & day incessantly praying for grace to us that we may repent, and for pardon when we doe, and for degrees of pardon beyond the capacities of our infirmities, and the merit of our sorrows & amendment, and this prayer he will continue till his second coming;
                        Hebr. 7.25. 
                     for he ever liveth to make intercession for us, and that we may know what it is in behalf of which he intercedes,2 Cor. 5.20. S. Paul tels us his designe [we are Embassadours for Christ, as though he did beseech you by us, we pray you in Christs stead to be reconciled to God; & what Christ prayes us to do, he prayes to God that we may do; that which he desires of us as his servants, he desires of God who is the fountain of the grace and powers unto us, and without whose assistance we can do nothing.
